learning_outcomes.en:
The students will:
1) understand the main theses and models of biosemiotics; 
2) know the historical development of biosemiotics;
3) interpret the typology of semiosis in living systems and the relationship between biosemiotics and semiotis of culture; 
4) discuss and apply the contemporary knowledge, methods and research questions in biosemiotic studies.

learning_outcomes.et:
Pärast kursuse läbimist üliõpilane:
1) mõistab biosemiootika põhiteese;
2) valdab ning analüüsib semioosi tüpoloogiat elussüsteemides;
3) arutleb ning rakendab kaasaegset teavet, metodoloogiat ning peamisi uurimisküsimusi biosemiootikas.

description.et:
I exam-colloqium. A small exam-test. In order to make it, one should know:
(1) the main contribution to biosemiotics of the scholars listed in Favareau's "Essential Readings in Biosemiotics" (at least those of chapters 2-11 and 14-21);
(2) the main content of 8 theses of biosemiotics as described in the article "Theses on biosemiotics" 2009 (file Saka.pdf in the study materials).
